        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/Whats-new/Speeches-and-articles/speeches_foreign/2010/maritim_disputes.html?id=614728" title="">
                        Managing the Arctic
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none">21 September 2010</h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Speech/article, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 21.09.2010]</p>
                <p>The Arctic agreement between Russia and Norway provides valuable lessons on trust and the long-range view, write  Sergej Lavrov, Russian Foreign Minister and Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre of Norway.  </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp534917556_wp477373900_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl00_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/press/news/2010/coastal_states_africa.html?id=614650" title="">
                        Norway signs agreement with coastal states in Africa
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Press release, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 21.09.2010]</p>
                <p>Minister of the Environment and International Development Erik Solheim will sign an agreement with six countries in Africa that will help them to gain jurisdiction over their own oil and gas resources. </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp534917556_wp477373900_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl01_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/Whats-new/news/2010/chd_fraud.html?id=613426" title="">
                        Centre for Humanitarian Dialogue in Geneva falls prey to fraud
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[News story, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 02.09.2010]</p>
                <p>The Ministry of Foreign Affairs became aware this summer that the Director of Finance and Administration at the Centre for Humanitarian Dialgoue in Geneva is suspected of fraud. The HD Centre is a Geneva-based foundation that works with the prevention and resolution of conflict. </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp534917556_wp477373900_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl02_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/Whats-new/news/2010/coastal_states.html?id=609558" title="">
                        Enhanced scientific cooperation among the coastal States of the Arctic Ocean
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[News story, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 24.06.2010]</p>
                <p>Senior officials of the five coastal States of the Arctic Ocean – Canada, Denmark/Greenland, the Russian Federation, the United States of America and Norway – met on 22 June 2010 in Oslo to hold informal discussions on their particular responsibilities in the field of conservation and management of fish stocks. </p>
                
                
